                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/524b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-02T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1284. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>,
                        <persName>Smith</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 132. Consider very important to arrange that vessels not touching American
                    ports proceeding to Spain from South America, Central America, Mexico, West
                    Indies, etc., be compelled call at Porto Rico for examination to avoid necessity
                    Allied blockade fleet requiring vessels proceed Kirkwall or Gibraltar for
                    examination. Confidently reported Mexico assembling quantity Mexican coal at
                    Tampico to enable Spanish vessels proceed direct between Mexico and Spain for
                    frank purpose of evading our jurisdiction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
